<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1927-06-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1927-06-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="117" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d117">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/9141½</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Coolidge</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rapid
                                        City, S. Dak.</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-06-23"><hi rend="italic">June 23,
                                1927</hi></date>.<lb/>[Received June 27.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: I have your letter,
                            together with the substance of the recent dispatch from Minister
                            MacMurray. I approve the suggestions made by the Minister and referred
                            to in your own letter, subject of course to your judgment on them.</p>
                        <p>Very truly yours,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Calvin Coolidge</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>